channel.title: How to get Macs Object Dock on XP
channel.description:
Lots of people love Macs ObjectDock , but they have a XP well some guys over at [b][url=http://Stardock.com]Stardock.com[/url][/b] made a program for these people.
[IMG]http://img69.imageshack.us/img69/152/firstno4.png[/img] This is a object dock *My object dock :)*
First your going to have to go to this site to download it: [url=http://www.download.com/ObjectDock/3000-2341_4-10529607.html?tag=lst-0-1]http://www.download.com/ObjectDock/3000-2341_4-10529607.html?tag=lst-0-1[/url]
Press download and follow the instructions [IMG]http://img113.imageshack.us/img113/7466/2ndik5.png[/img]
Once you finish downloading you can go and play around with the settings.. [IMG]http://img242.imageshack.us/img242/9607/3rdxu7.png[/img] ________________________________________________________________________________________
Now you want to get better looking icons eh? Well there is a site just for that [url=http://www.wincustomize.com/Skins.aspx?LibID=29]http://www.wincustomize.com/Skins.aspx?LibID=29[/url]
You can go there and look around for icons once you do find a icon how do you install it?
Go to the icon you want to change on the Object Dock and right click it, choose Dock Entry Properties.. [IMG]http://img242.imageshack.us/img242/9347/4thra0.png[/img]
Press change image and find where your icon is [IMG]http://img60.imageshack.us/img60/8471/5thhm5.png[/img]
And your finished! You have a great looking Mac Object Dock ;)
Here are some Icons I have.. [IMG]http://img244.imageshack.us/img244/5273/photoshopcs2mn2.png[/img] [IMG]http://img79.imageshack.us/img79/7732/msnmenmetalicki6.png[/img] [IMG]http://img50.imageshack.us/img50/2559/firefox2005iconpngxc1.png[/img]
I'll post more later..
_______________________________________________________________________________
[b]The people that made this program also have some other nice and helpful programs you can go check them out at
[url=http://Stardock.com]Stardock.com[/url]
